==================================================
# MudBlazor Components Overview
==================================================

### 1. MudText (Text Component)
   - Displays styled text based on Material Design typography.
   - Properties:
     - `Typo`: Defines text style (e.g., `Typo.h3`, `Typo.h5`, `Typo.h4`).
   - Example:
     ```razor
     <MudText Typo="Typo.h3">Heading</MudText>
     ```

### 2. MudButton (Button Component)
   - Represents an interactive button with customizable styles.
   - Properties:
     - `OnClick`: Event handler triggered when clicked.
     - `Variant`: Defines button style:
       - `Variant.Filled` → Solid button.
       - `Variant.Outlined` → Button with an outline.
       - `Variant.Text` → No background or outline.
     - `Color`: Defines the button color (e.g., `Color.Primary`, `Color.Secondary`).
   - Example:
     ```razor
     <MudButton OnClick="MyFunction" Variant="Variant.Outlined" Color="Color.Success">
         Click Me
     </MudButton>
     ```

### 3. MudAlert (Alert Component)
   - Displays a message box for notifications, warnings, or errors.
   - Properties:
     - `Severity`: Defines alert type:
       - `Severity.Info` → Informational message.
       - `Severity.Success` → Success message.
       - `Severity.Warning` → Warning message.
       - `Severity.Error` → Error message.
   - Example:
     ```razor
     <MudAlert Severity="Severity.Warning">
         Warning! Check your input.
     </MudAlert>
     ```

### 4. Additional MudBlazor Features Used:
   - **`<strong>` (HTML Bold)**: Used inside `<MudText>` to emphasize labels.
   - **`@if(...) {}` (Razor Conditionals)**: Dynamically displays elements based on conditions.
   - ** Utility Classes**:
     - `.mt-4` → Adds top margin spacing.

